There are people in this country who are sworn enemies of progress. They sit in critical decision-making positions, chewing public money and belching monotonous sound bites.
They appear on television with tough speeches and a dictionary of bad jokes. On other days, they address the media wearing a stone face covered with a closed mind, and when journalists ask them tough questions, they say they aren’t responsible for anyone who doesn’t eat from their houses.



