This week has been slippery for this category. A 28-year-old doctor died in the line of duty, and not even the President has bothered to open the kitchen door to have a discussion with the heat inside, and it isn’t because he doesn’t have a fireman’s licence.
It is understandable he is no longer on social media, and we would’ve excused him for being behind news, had he not sent a congratulatory message to the President of Ghana for winning a second term without promising to revisit the Judiciary.



