That’s not someone who is behind news. The message from State House is clear; that the President has exercised his constitutional freedom to choose his friends, and doctors aren’t among them.
Crocodile tears
Had this been an election month, the entire government machinery would have been dispatched to go commiserate with the family, friends and the doctors’ fraternity. Crocodile tears would have been shed, and the Kenya Medical Practitioners Pharmacists and Dentists Union (KMPDU) would have been promised a comprehensive insurance in six months’ time.
State House would have sent someone to Afya House with a giant axe to greet the Health minister, and the governor of the jurisdiction where the young doctor was working would by now have been speaking in tongues at an impeachment trial.



