Instead, these people are still walking around in a manner likely to suggest they haven’t learnt anything from their lack of leadership. We saw the Machakos governor apportioning blame to the national government, which in turn handed over the skunk to the Kenya Medical Supplies Authority, who picked the cue and blamed some shadowy Deep State for sending them death threats. The trail has since gone cold as we wait for the National Registration Bureau to give us the ID Number of this person called Deep State.
When doctors appeared along Cathedral Road this week for an evening vigil to remember their colleagues who have died from Covid-19, the Health ministry did not even bother to send a junior officer to commiserate with them, despite the vigil happening right under the nose of Afya House. Magical Kenya has been selling Kenya as the undisputed home of the Big Five, but it looks like government officials would rather die than lead the pack right now.
Things would have been different had a Kenyan doctor discovered the cure for indecisiveness. The Health CS would have invited the media for another dose of memes to celebrate the happy news, hopping from one media house to another asking whether a vaccine would have achieved the same feat.



